comments.bodyText:
I think it would've been possible to chain onChangeToken if it's component with render prop instead of HOC
class Dashboard extends Component {
  onChangeToken() {
    ...
  }

  renderDashboard(loginInfo) {
    return (...)
  }

  render() {
    return (
      <Auth
        onChangeToken={this.onChangeToken}
        render={this.renderDashboard}
      />
    )
  }
}
The onChangeToken in Auth component (currently withAuth HOC) should also call this.props.onChangeToken, after setting its own state.
You could also pass Client down with this.props.onChangeToken so it's not leaking (although I'm not so sure, is Client related to auth?)

